You mention that you are not working with personal data. Are you sure that there is no personal data defined as "any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person" in your files? This includes pseudonymous data where there is still information that may lead to the identification of the participants by you or by others. Some of the data you mention is available under restricted acces, suggesting they contain personal data. If you work with personal data please fill a PRET form to register these in the KU Leuven processing of personal data register as required under the GDPR. For more information please have a look at https://research.kuleuven.be/en/associatienet/ethics/guidance/personaldata, you can contact pret@kuleuven.be if you have any further questions.
